"The user browses View 1 at the [Overview] level and learns about the overall academic profile of students displayed in tabular format. Next, the user selects specific departments of interest in View 2 at the [Exploration] level, which filters data dynamically across other views. The user further drills into specific demographics in View 3 and observes correlations between age and extracurricular activities. In View 4 at the [Detail] level, the user investigates major-minor combinations using heat maps, and finally, in View 5, they analyze the overall division proportions using pie charts at the [Insight] level."